cystic
fibrosis
in
two
black
children
with
sickle
cell
anemia
sickle
cell
anemia
and
cystic
fibrosis
are
the
most
frequent
lethal
inherited
diseases
in
the
black
and
white
population
respectively
the
occurrence
of
both
diseases
in
the
same
individual
has
not
been
reported
in
the
literature
this
report
presents
two
such
patients
and
poses
questions
concerning
the
possible
clinical
implications
of
the
simultaneous
occurrence
of
both
diseases
